<inglise> Council Regulation (EEC) No 1332/92 of 18 May 1992 introducing specific measures for table olives </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1332/92, millega kehtestatakse lauaoliivide suhtes erimeetmed 18. mai 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposals from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekuid, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the production of table olives is a major economic activity, especially in certain Mediterranean regions of the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: oliivide kasvatamine on olulise t&auml;htsusega majandustegevus, eriti &uuml;henduse Vahemere-&auml;&auml;rsetes piirkondades; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the situation on the market for table olives is poorly adjusted to commercial requirements with regard to both the conditions of production and the conditions of processing and marketing; </inglise>
<eesti> olukorda lauaoliivide turul ei ole kohandatud turun&otilde;uetega tootmistingimuste ning t&ouml;&ouml;tlemis- ja turustamistingimuste osas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas that situation has given rise to an imbalance between supply and demand, resulting in the formation of surpluses in recent years; </inglise>
<eesti> selline olukord on tekitanud pakkumise ja n&otilde;udluse tasakaalustamatuse, mis on p&otilde;hjustanud &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;kide teket viimastel aastatel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas there are prospects of increasing consumption, particularly through better information to existing or potential users and a more stringent adjustment of production to meet the requirements of consumers; </inglise>
<eesti> on v&auml;ljavaateid tarbimise suurendamiseks eelk&otilde;ige teavitades paremini olemasolevaid v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalikke kasutajaid ja kohandades toodangut t&auml;psemalt tarbijate n&otilde;udmistele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the various trade groups in the sector should play a special role in implementing means of developing consumption; </inglise>
<eesti> erinevatel sektori tegevusalar&uuml;hmadel peaks olema tarbimist arendavate meetmete rakendamisel eriline osa; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made for specific measures to increase the consumption of table olives to be encouraged by means of a financial contribution by the Community to these measures; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada erimeetmed lauaoliivide tarbimise suurendamiseks nii, et &uuml;hendus osaleb nende meetmete rahastamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to permit producer groups or associations thereof which produce and market table olives to concentrate supply and to stagger quantities released to the market by means in particular of suitable storage capacity, such groups or associations should be encouraged, to set up working capital; whereas, to that end, provision should be made for financial contributions from the Member State and the Community, with a ceiling determined by reference to the value of production marketed by the producer groups and associations thereof over a given marketing year; </inglise>
<eesti> et v&otilde;imaldada lauaoliive kasvatavatel ja turustavatel tootjar&uuml;hmadel ja tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;hendustel tarne koondamist ja j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgulist turule laskmist eelk&otilde;ige sobiva laomahu abil, tuleks selliste r&uuml;hmade ja &uuml;henduste puhul soodustada k&auml;ibekapitali moodustamist; sel eesm&auml;rgil tuleks ette n&auml;ha liikmesriikide ja &uuml;henduse rahaline toetus, mille &uuml;lemm&auml;&auml;r m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks asjaomasel majandusaastal tootjar&uuml;hmade ja tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;henduste turustatud toodangu v&auml;&auml;rtuse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the situation obtaining in producer Member States, cooperatives and associations thereof should be allowed to qualify for that aid for a limited period; </inglise>
<eesti> arvestades tootjaliikmesriikides valitsevat olukorda, tuleks &uuml;histutele ja &uuml;histute &uuml;hendustele anda nimetatud abi piiratud aja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas such measures are intended to achieve the objectives of Article 39 of the Treaty; whereas there should be provision for the Community to make a financial contribution to the implementation of the measures in question through the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF), Guarantee Section, </inglise>
<eesti> selliste meetmete eesm&auml;rk on asutamislepingu artikli 39 eesm&auml;rkide saavutamine; k&otilde;nealuste meetmete rakendamiseks tuleks ette n&auml;ha &uuml;henduse rahaline toetus Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi (EAGGF) tagatisrahastu kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall contribute up to 60 % of the cost of measures to develop the consumption of table olives in the Community, put forward and implemented by representative groups bringing together various types of activity in the sector. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus osaleb kuni 60% ulatuses selliste sektori erinevaid tegevusliike koondavate esindavate r&uuml;hmade esitatud ja rakendatud meetmete rahastamisel, millega arendatakse lauaoliivide tarbimist &uuml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> The representative nature of the groups shall be assessed in the light of the objective to be achieved. </inglise>
<eesti> Gruppide esindavust hinnatakse taotletava eesm&auml;rgi j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The measures referred to in Article 1 shall be intended to: </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 nimetatud meetmete eesm&auml;rgiks on: </eesti>
<inglise> - promote the quality of the product, mainly through the carrying out of market studies and research into the production of olives with a low salt content, </inglise>
<eesti> - toodete kvaliteedi parandamine turu-uuringute ja madala soolasisaldusega oliivide tootmise alase uurimist&ouml;&ouml; abil, </eesti>
<inglise> - develop new forms of packaging, </inglise>
<eesti> - uute pakkimismeetodite arendamine, </eesti>
<inglise> - distribute advice on marketing to the various economic operators in the sector, </inglise>
<eesti> - turundusn&otilde;uannete levitamine selle sektori mitmesuguste ettev&otilde;tjate seas, </eesti>
<inglise> - encourage publicity and public relations, including the organization of, and participation in, trade fairs and other commercial events. </inglise>
<eesti> - reklaami ja suhtekorralduse edendamine, sealhulgas messide ja muude kaubanduslike &uuml;rituste organiseerimine ja neil osalemine. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Measures under Article 1 may not be geared towards commercial brands or refer to a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 nimetatud meetmed ei v&otilde;i olla suunatud kaubam&auml;rkidele ega viidata teatavale liikmesriigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall grant specific aid to groups or associations thereof of producers of table olives falling within CN codes 0709 90 31, 0709 90 39, 0710 80 10, 0711 20, ex 0712 90 90, ex 2001 90 80, ex 2004 90 30 and 2005 70 00 which fulfil the conditions set out in Articles 5 and 6 (1) and (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1360/78 (3) and which constitute working capital with the objective of stabilizing supply by ensuring in particular the financing of storage required for the suitable release to the market of the product. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid annavad eriabi CN-koodide 0709 90 31, 0709 90 39, 0710 80 10, 0711 20, ex 0712 90 90, ex 2001 90 80, ex 2004 90 30 ja 2005 70 00 alla kuuluvate lauaoliivide tootjar&uuml;hmadele v&otilde;i tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;hendustele, mis vastavad m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1360/78 (3) artiklis 5 ja artikli 6 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 esitatud tingimustele ja mis moodustavad k&auml;ibekapitali eesm&auml;rgiga stabiliseerida pakkumist eelk&otilde;ige tagades toote sobival viisil turule laskmiseks vajaliku ladustamise rahastamise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The specific aid referred to in paragraph 1 shall be granted once only, subject to the capital being financed as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud eriabi antakse ainult &uuml;ks kord eeldusel, et kapitali rahastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - 45 % by the producer group or association thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> - 45% ulatuses tootjar&uuml;hmade v&otilde;i tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;henduste poolt, </eesti>
<inglise> - 10 % by aid from the Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> - 10% ulatuses liikmesriigi antud abist. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community contribution shall amount to 45 % of the capital. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus rahastab 45% kapitalist. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the overall financial commitment of the Member State and the Community may not exceed 10 % of the value of production marketed by the producer group or association thereof in one marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide ja &uuml;henduse rahaliste kohustuste kogusumma ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 10% &uuml;hel majandusaastal tootjar&uuml;hmade v&otilde;i tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;henduste turustatud toodangu v&auml;&auml;rtusest. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> For purposes of the granting of the aid referred to in paragraph 1, the cooperatives and associations thereof set up in accordance with the legislation in force in the sector concerned shall be considered, for a maximum period of three years, as being equivalent to the producer groups or associations thereof referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud abi andmisel loetakse vastavalt asjaomase sektori kehtivatele &otilde;igusaktidele moodustatud &uuml;histud v&otilde;i &uuml;histute &uuml;hendused k&otilde;ige rohkem kolmeks aastaks v&otilde;rdseteks l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud tootjar&uuml;hmadega v&otilde;i tootjar&uuml;hmade &uuml;hendustega. </eesti>
<inglise> In that event, the cooperatives or associations thereof shall institute a guarantee to ensure repayment of the aid received, should the obligations referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 not be fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nesoleval juhul esitavad &uuml;histud v&otilde;i &uuml;histute &uuml;hendused tagatise saadud abi tagasimaksmise kohta juhuks, kui l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 osutatud kohustusi ei t&auml;ideta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The part-financing of the measures referred to in Article 1 and the aid provided for in Article 3 shall be regarded as intervention measures intended to stabilize the agricultural markets pursuant to Article 3 (1) of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 (4). </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 osutatud meetmete osaline rahastamine ja artiklis 3 etten&auml;htud abi loetakse p&otilde;llumajandusturgude stabiliseerimiseks etten&auml;htud sekkumismeetmeteks vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (4) artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 1. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall be financed from the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF), Guarantee Section. </inglise>
<eesti> Meetmeid rahastab Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi (EAGGF) tagatisrahastu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with the procedure provided for in Article 38 of Regulation No 136/66/EEC (5), the Commission shall: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 136/66/EM&Uuml; (5) artiklis 38 s&auml;testatud korras komisjon: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) define the measures provided for in Article 2 of this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> a) m&auml;&auml;ratleb k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 2 etten&auml;htud meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) adopt detailed rules for the application of this Regulation; such detailed rules shall entail measures to monitor the use of the financial aid from the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> b) v&otilde;tab vastu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakendamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad; sellised &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad sisaldavad meetmeid &uuml;henduse rahalise abi kasutamise j&auml;relevalveks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
